This paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category as it discusses the analysis of evolutionary algorithms. It could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as drift analysis is a tool for analysing search heuristics. Additionally, it could be classified under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as these fields often use evolutionary algorithms. Finally, it could also be classified under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as the analysis of algorithms is an important aspect of software engineering.
